courses.name: Python for Data Science and Machine Learning Bootcamp
courses.description: Learn how to use NumPy, Pandas, Seaborn , Matplotlib , Plotly , Scikit-Learn , Machine Learning, Tensorflow , and more!
courses.content: Introduction to SQL: Learn SQL fundamentals such as JOINs, Aggregations, and Subqueries. Learn how to use SQL to answer complex business problems; Introduction to Python Programming: Learn Python programming fundamentals such as data structures, variables, loops, and functions. Learn to work with data using libraries like NumPy and Pandas; Introduction to Version Control: Learn how to use version control and share your work with other people in the data science industry
courses.review: This was my first course in Udemy, and with this instructor. This was an excellent first class to jump into the world of data science. All of the explanations were clear, and you can tell the instructor truly cares about software education.

videos.name: Lession 1: Java Variables and Methods
videos.description: Analysis of java basic variables and methods
videos.script: Historically, the older approach was to provide students with a beautiful, readable, and efficient cursive as a standard script for learning. Students were supposed to bring their writing closer and closer to this perfect model. In the first third of the 20th century, type teachers such as Rudolf von Larisch[1] and Ludwig Sütterlin[1] changed this traditional approach by defining the teaching script as a starting point instead of a target model
